data.caption: The Parenting for Liberation community gathered over the weekend for a joyous Kwanzaa celebration! Kwanzaa honors African heritage and here the community is seen lighting the mishumaa saba, or seven candles, which represent the seven principles of Kwanzaa: unity, self-determination, collective work and responsibility, cooperative economics, purpose, creativity and faith. #HappyHolidays #MoreTogether
In Filipino culture, parol lanterns are hung during Christmas time to symbolize how light triumphs over darkness, as well as a spirit of hope and goodwill. #MoreTogether

Happy Hanukkah! Members of the Facebook Group All Jewish Holidays love connecting with family, friends, and the Atlanta community to celebrate the holidays. Here Josh helps his son light the candles using the shammash - one candle for each night of Hanukkah. #HappyHanakkuh #MoreTogether
Holiday traditions can bring a sense of home, no matter where you are. Share this card with those you love to wish them a happy holiday season! #HappyHolidays #MoreTogether
This World Kindness Day, common_wild is here to remind us to be kind to ourselves. Tag someone who deserves a little extra love. #WorldKindnessDay #MoreTogether
